ferred because of their high-power efficiency and density. The power yield of BLDCs can be limited by varying the voltage applied to ESCs [11]. In accordance with the fundamental principles governing electric motors, the resultant mechanical power (P) is evaluated by considering M as the torque which is measured in Newton-meters (Nm), ω as the angular velocity which is expressed in radians per second (rad/s), and n as the rotational speed denoted in revolutions per minute (RPM) [12]. Propellers are coupled on top of these motors that provide lift to the aircraft by spinning and generating airflows which further accelerate mass in one direction, counteracting the force of",
